      "title": "Quoting Sam Altman",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/20/sam-altman/#atom-everything",
      "source": "Simon Willison",
      "published": "2026-07-20T03:47:59+00:00",
      "summary_raw": "We have been having extensive discussions around open source strategy. We will discuss it more at our next board meeting, but one thing we\u2019d like to do soon is to create a language model with the approximate capability of GPT-3 that can run locally on consumer hardware and release that. We\u2019d like to do it soon, before Stability or someone else does. In general, we think this helps discourage others from releasing similarly-powerful models, and makes it harder for new efforts to get funded.\n&mdash; Sam Altman, Email to OpenAI's board, October 1, 2022 - exposed in Musk v. Altman (2026)\n\n    Tags: ai-ethics, sam-altman, generative-ai, openai, ai, llms"
